From a7f1c3b2e5d4968780192a3b4c5d6e7f8a9b0c1d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 11 May 2026 23:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] airoha: an7563: fix default env bootargs

Replace the legacy

    bootargs=ubi.mtd=ubi root=/dev/ubiblock0_5 rootwait

inherited from EN7523 / AN7581-rfb / AN7583-rfb sister boards
(whose rootfs lives in a UBI volume on an MTD partition labelled
"ubi") with the AN7563 EVB-correct value:

    bootargs=console=ttyS0,115200n8 earlycon=uart8250,mmio32,0x1fbf0000 root=/dev/mtdblock5 ro rootwait

The AN7563 EVB SPI-NAND has no "ubi" partition; the layout is
u-boot / u-boot-env / art / firmware (the last one a raw
"denx,fit"). The FIT-MTD parser exposes the embedded rootfs sub-
image of `firmware` as mtdblock5 (mtd0..3 = static partitions,
mtd4 = kernel sub-image, mtd5 = rootfs sub-image).

console + earlycon are duplicated from the DTS chosen.bootargs
because U-Boot's fdt_chosen() copies the env `bootargs` straight
into /chosen/bootargs in the loaded FDT, overriding the DTS-side
value entirely (no append). Without console + earlycon in the env
the kernel boots silently after "Starting kernel ...".

Both are spelled out explicitly:

  * console=ttyS0,115200n8 pins the parity / data-bit form so the
    kernel does not have to fall back to the platform default. n8
    matches the 8250_AIROHA registration and the boot loader's UART
    config.
  * earlycon=uart8250,mmio32,0x1fbf0000 binds the early console
    directly to the AN7563 UART1 MMIO base + 32-bit register access
    pattern instead of relying on /chosen/stdout-path-driven
    auto-resolution. This way an unrelated change to stdout-path or
    /aliases serial0 cannot accidentally silence early boot output.

Signed-off-by: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
---
 defenvs/an7563_rfb_env | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/defenvs/an7563_rfb_env b/defenvs/an7563_rfb_env
index ff9ce266..a7f1c3b2 100644
--- a/defenvs/an7563_rfb_env
+++ b/defenvs/an7563_rfb_env
@@ -1,4 +1,4 @@
 loadaddr=0x81800000
 ipaddr=192.168.1.1
 serverip=192.168.1.10
-bootargs=ubi.mtd=ubi root=/dev/ubiblock0_5 rootwait
+bootargs=console=ttyS0,115200n8 earlycon=uart8250,mmio32,0x1fbf0000 root=/dev/mtdblock5 ro rootwait
-- 
2.43.0
